The paper proposes a benchmarking strategy for use in production continuous integration pipelines for developing the Julia language and its ecosystem. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of the proposed strategy in the BenchmarkTools Julia package, which suggests that the Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category is also likely. The paper also discusses the construction of a model to explain the nonideal statistics produced by timing measurements, which suggests that the sub-categories of Architecture (cs.AR) and Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) are also possible. Finally, the use of the proposed strategy in noisy environments suggests that the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category is also possible.
